<p class="p">The principles of evaluating the percentage of open caps were in accordance with development of the umbrella‐like form of the cap followed by detachment of veil. The percent open caps were measured using known number of mushrooms based on Equation (
 <xref rid="fsn31000-disp-0001" ref-type="disp-formula" class="xref">1</xref>):
 <disp-formula id="fsn31000-disp-0001" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(1)</label>
  <math id="nlm-math-1" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mo class="mo">%</mo>
    <mspace width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
    <mtext class="mtext">Open</mtext>
    <mspace width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
    <mtext class="mtext">caps</mtext>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">N</mi>
      <mtext class="mtext">oc</mtext>
     </msub>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">N</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">t</mi>
     </msub>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">×</mo>
    <mn class="mn">100</mn>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <italic class="italic">N</italic>
 <sub class="sub">oc</sub> = number of opened cap mushrooms; 
 <italic class="italic">N</italic>
 <sub class="sub">t</sub> = total number of mushrooms.
</p>
